Contribution functionsContribution functions act a bit like ES6 symbols, or 'tagging interfaces' in
Java speak. They don't do anything themselves, but allow a component to interact
with a layout without being tighly coupled with it.In the most basic scenario, we define the contribution functions right along
our layout and also import them from there in our components:Layout.jsfunction Header(){}
function Footer(){}

function MyLayout(){
    // use Header and Footer here
}

export {
    Header,
    Footer,
    MyLayout
}
Component.jsimport { Header, Footer } from './Layout'

function MyComponent(){
    // use Header and Footer here
}
If our site has many layouts and many components contributing to those
layouts, it will probably pay off to place the contribution functions in a
separate file and reuse them where needed:Sections.jsfunction Header(){}
function Footer(){}

export {
    Header,
    Footer
}
Layout.jsimport { Header, Footer } from './Sections'

function MyLayout(){
    // use Header and Footer here
}
export {
    MyLayout
}
Component.jsimport { Header, Footer } from './Sections'

function MyComponent(){
    // use Header and Footer here
}
AttributesappendWhen set, any contributions found will be appended to any existing
default elements / prior contributions, instead of replacing them (default)prependWhen set, any contributions found will be prepended before any existing
default elements / prior contributions, instead of replacing them (default)Example(assuming Header is a contribution function)function MyComponent(){return (


            This will be appended to the header section instead of replacing it


        Stuff here ends up in the main section

)}
